      "source": [
        "1.1\n",
        "\n",
        "Leverage is defined as the ratio of exposure to the capital committed. So leverage less than 1 means that our exposure is less than the capital. So we are not utilising our entire capital. In this context, it makes financial sense in volatile markets so that we don't risk our entire capital. It also allows us to diversify our investments and manage risk. However, the other capital is left unutilized, which is a possible downside.\n",
        "In our backtesting engine, currently we are only generating 0, 1 or -1 signals. This is unlike real life where we can choose to buy/sell more or less of any stock. To simulate this, we can use leverage for position sizing. We might choose to reduce the leverage when the trend is weak, and increase it when it is strong. This way, similar to real life, we can have more or less on stake by changing our position size."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Hy2lhG-7wcWv"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "1.2\n",
        "\n",
        "A static stoploss is fixed. It doesn't move with the share price. That is, regardless of how the share moves, the trade will only be exited (via the stoploss) when the price hits or goes below the strike price fixed at the beginning of the trade.\n",
        "A trailing stoploss however, is dynamic, and moves up with the share price. So, if the share moves up, the trailing stoploss will also move up. So it is possible that the stoploss is triggered much above the original strike or even buying price. (The TSL does not move down, that would defeat the purpose of a stoploss)\n",
        "In trade risk management, a trailing stop loss rides a trend, basically restricting the drawdown, whereas the static stoploss only exits according to the price set during the trade.\n",
        "For a trending market, a trailing stoploss may be more sensitive to noise and exit early, especially if it is too tight, as then even if the stock is tranding up and is likely to do so, a slight decrease may trigger the TSL. The SSL is less sensitive to noise and will only trigger when the share price drops as low as it. However, in case of a trend reversal, the SSL would trigger too late and the profits would not have materialized, whereas the TSL would have locked in the profits.\n",
        "For a volatile market, similar is true. A TSL may trigger too soon due to some noise which is common in volatile markets, but would lock in the profits in case the share price increases. The SSL may trigger too late and miss out on possible profits, but is less sensitive to the noise."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "CMJNgP7Y-xFJ"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "1.3\n",
        "A trailing take profit is basically just a trailing stop loss that is activated after the initial take profit is reached. So implementing it separately is not necessary, as the TSL functionality is almost the same."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "VxLhPN2je2g6"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "1.4\n",
        "\n",
        "A trade may remain open even after the price falls below the set stop-loss\n",
        "level in the following cases.\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Slippage: In fast markets in which prices change very suddenly, or in markets that are not liquid, the position may be held even beyond the stop loss level. By the time the order is carried out, the price may have slipped much further in a fast market. In an illiquid market, the market order may not have been completed.\n",
        "2. Gaps or Overnight Changes: In case there are sudden changes causing gaps or there are changes in the stock price overnight, the market order would not be carried out at the stop loss price, especially if it is a limit order, it would not be carried out at all.\n",
        "3. System/broker/manual delays."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "HK8QU-lxgn2s"
      }
    },

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Install and Import Required Libraries\n",
        "\n",
        "!pip install yfinance mplfinance\n",
        "\n",
        "import yfinance as yf\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import mplfinance as mpf\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Download 5 years of data for Reliance\n",
        "data = yf.download('RELIANCE.NS', period='5y', interval='1d')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Flatten multi-level columns if any\n",
        "data.columns.name = None  # remove 'Ticker' label\n",
        "data.reset_index(inplace=True)\n",
        "data.columns = [col if not isinstance(col, tuple) else col[0] for col in data.columns]\n",
        "\n",
        "# defining pattern identification functions\n",
        "\n",
        "def doji(open_, high, low, close):\n",
        "    body = abs(close - open_)\n",
        "    range_ = high - low\n",
        "    return body < 0.1 * range_\n",
        "\n",
        "def hammer(open_, high, low, close):\n",
        "    body = abs(close - open_)\n",
        "    lower_wick = min(open_, close) - low\n",
        "    upper_wick = high - max(open_, close)\n",
        "    return (body <= 0.1 * (high - low)) and (lower_wick >= 2 * body) and (upper_wick <= 0.1 * (high - low))\n",
        "\n",
        "def bullish_engulfing(prev_open, prev_close, curr_open, curr_close):\n",
        "    return (prev_close < prev_open) and (curr_close > curr_open) and (curr_open < prev_close) and (curr_close > prev_open)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Identifying pattern occurance\n",
        "data['Doji'] = data.apply(lambda row: doji(row['Open'], row['High'], row['Low'], row['Close']), axis=1)\n",
        "data['Hammer'] = data.apply(lambda row: hammer(row['Open'], row['High'], row['Low'], row['Close']), axis=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# For Engulfing (requires previous row)\n",
        "engulfing_flags = [False]\n",
        "for i in range(1, len(data)):\n",
        "    prev = data.iloc[i-1]\n",
        "    curr = data.iloc[i]\n",
        "    engulfing_flags.append(bullish_engulfing(prev['Open'], prev['Close'], curr['Open'], curr['Close']))\n",
        "data['Engulfing'] = engulfing_flags\n",
        "\n",
        "# Ensure 'Date' is datetime and set as index\n",
        "data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'])\n",
        "data.set_index('Date', inplace=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "add_plot = []\n",
        "\n",
        "# Mark Doji candles with blue circles\n",
        "doji_markers = mpf.make_addplot(data['Close'][data['Doji']], type='scatter', markersize=100, marker='o', color='blue')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Mark Hammer candles with green upward triangles\n",
        "hammer_markers = mpf.make_addplot(data['Close'][data['Hammer']], type='scatter', markersize=100, marker='^', color='green')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Mark Bullish Engulfing with orange stars\n",
        "engulfing_markers = mpf.make_addplot(data['Close'][data['Engulfing']], type='scatter', markersize=150, marker='*', color='orange')\n",
        "\n",
        "add_plot += [doji_markers, hammer_markers, engulfing_markers]\n",
        "# Example: last 100 days\n",
        "data_recent = data.tail(100)\n",
        "\n",
        "mpf.plot(data_recent,\n",
        "         type='candle',\n",
        "         style='charles',\n",
        "         volume=True,\n",
        "         addplot=[  # use sliced marker plots too\n",
        "            mpf.make_addplot(data_recent['Close'].where(data_recent['Doji']), type='scatter', markersize=100, marker='o', color='blue'),\n",
        "            mpf.make_addplot(data_recent['Close'].where(data_recent['Hammer']), type='scatter', markersize=100, marker='^', color='green'),\n",
        "            mpf.make_addplot(data_recent['Close'].where(data_recent['Engulfing']), type='scatter', markersize=150, marker='*', color='orange'),\n",
        "         ],\n",
        "         title='Candlestick Patterns (Recent 100 Days)',\n",
        "         figsize=(16, 8))"
      ],

        "# Win-Rate Calculation Function\n",
        "def compute_win_rate(df, pattern_col, n):\n",
        "    indices = df[df[pattern_col]].index\n",
        "    wins = 0\n",
        "    for idx in indices:\n",
        "        # Get the integer location of the current timestamp in the index\n",
        "        idx_loc = df.index.get_loc(idx)\n",
        "        # Check if the index location n steps ahead is within the DataFrame length\n",
        "        if idx_loc + n < len(df):\n",
        "            # Access data using the integer location for slicing and indexing\n",
        "            ret = df.iloc[idx_loc + n]['Close'] - df.iloc[idx_loc]['Close']\n",
        "            if ret > 0:\n",
        "                wins += 1\n",
        "    total = len(indices)\n",
        "    return 100 * wins / total if total > 0 else 0\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "SxUFA3dlYe-t"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def baseline_win_rate(df, n, M):\n",
        "    # Generate random integer indices within the valid range for starting points\n",
        "    random_start_indices = np.random.choice(len(df) - n, M, replace=False)\n",
        "    wins = sum(df.iloc[i + n]['Close'] > df.iloc[i]['Close'] for i in random_start_indices)\n",
        "    return 100 * wins / M\n",
        "\n",
        "# Initialize empty list for final results\n",
        "final_results = []\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate pattern win-rates\n",
        "for pattern in ['Doji', 'Hammer', 'Engulfing']:\n",
        "    row = {'Pattern': pattern}\n",
        "    for n in [3, 5]:\n",
        "        row[f'n={n}'] = compute_win_rate(data, pattern, n)\n",
        "    final_results.append(row)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate baseline win-rates\n",
        "M = int(data[['Doji', 'Hammer', 'Engulfing']].sum().mean())\n",
        "baseline_results = [\n",
        "    {'Pattern': 'Baseline', f'n=3': baseline_win_rate(data, 3, M), f'n=5': baseline_win_rate(data, 5, M)}\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Combine baseline + pattern results\n",
        "df_results = pd.DataFrame(baseline_results + final_results)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ],

        "\n",
        "Chart Interpretation: Strategy X Overview\n",
        "Main Technical Indicators Used\n",
        "Heiken Ashi Candles\n",
        "\n",
        "Smooths price action, helping to identify trend direction more clearly than regular candlesticks.\n",
        "\n",
        "Bullish candles often lack lower wicks; bearish candles often lack upper wicks.\n",
        "\n",
        "Supertrend (10,3)\n",
        "\n",
        "A trend-following indicator.\n",
        "\n",
        "Green line: Uptrend zone.\n",
        "\n",
        "Red line: Downtrend zone.\n",
        "\n",
        "Money Flow Index (MFI - 14)\n",
        "\n",
        "Combines price and volume to gauge buying/selling pressure.\n",
        "\n",
        "Focus is on the direction of MFI rather than strict overbought (80) or oversold (20) thresholds.\n",
        "\n",
        "Crosses around 50 are especially important:\n",
        "\n",
        "Crossing above 50 → Increasing buying pressure.\n",
        "\n",
        "Crossing below 50 → Increasing selling pressure.\n",
        "\n",
        "Visual Annotations\n",
        "Green Arrows → Potential Buy signals (Supertrend turns green, MFI rising, bullish Heiken Ashi).\n",
        "\n",
        "Red Arrows → Potential Sell signals (Supertrend turns red, MFI falling, bearish Heiken Ashi).\n",
        "\n",
        "Green Ovals → MFI rising through 50, indicating accumulation.\n",
        "\n",
        "Red Ovals → MFI dropping through 50, indicating distribution.\n",
        "\n",
        "Trend Zones\n",
        "Uptrend Zone:\n",
        "Supertrend is green; Heiken Ashi candles are bullish (typically green with no lower wicks).\n",
        "\n",
        "Downtrend Zone:\n",
        "Supertrend is red; Heiken Ashi candles are bearish (typically red with no upper wicks).\n",
        "\n",
        "Sideways/Neutral Zone:\n",
        "Price hovers around Supertrend; MFI lacks strong direction.\n",
        "\n",

        "\n",
        "Strategy Rules\n",
        "Entry Rules\n",
        "A. Long (Buy) Entry\n",
        "Enter long when all of the following are true:\n",
        "\n",
        "Supertrend flips to green.\n",
        "\n",
        "Heiken Ashi candles turn bullish (green body, no lower wick).\n",
        "\n",
        "MFI shows increasing buying pressure, ideally crossing above 50.\n",
        "\n",
        "Timing: Enter on the close of the next candle after all conditions are met.\n",
        "\n",
        "B. Short (Sell) Entry\n",
        "Enter short when all of the following are true:\n",
        "\n",
        "Supertrend flips to red.\n",
        "\n",
        "Heiken Ashi candles turn bearish (red body, no upper wick).\n",
        "\n",
        "MFI shows increasing selling pressure, ideally crossing below 50.\n",
        "\n",
        "Timing: Enter on the close of the next candle after confirmation.\n",
        "\n",
        "Exit Rules\n",
        "Exit Long Position when:\n",
        "\n",
        "Supertrend turns red, or\n",
        "\n",
        "MFI begins falling from high levels (e.g., from >60 to below 50), or\n",
        "\n",
        "Bearish Heiken Ashi reversal candle appears (red body with long upper wick).\n",
        "\n",
        "Exit Short Position when:\n",
        "\n",
        "Supertrend turns green, or\n",
        "\n",
        "MFI begins rising from low levels (e.g., from <40 to near 50), or\n",
        "\n",
        "Bullish Heiken Ashi reversal candle appears (green body with long lower wick).\n",

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "#download data\n",
        "import yfinance as yf\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "def download_flat_yf(ticker, start, end, interval):\n",
        "    data = yf.download(ticker, start=start, end=end, interval=interval, progress=False)\n",
        "    if isinstance(data.columns, pd.MultiIndex):\n",
        "        data = data.xs(ticker, axis=1, level=1)\n",
        "    data.columns.name = None\n",
        "    data.reset_index(inplace=True)\n",
        "    data.columns = [col.lower() for col in data.columns]\n",
        "    if data.columns[0] in ['date', 'datetime']:\n",
        "        data.rename(columns={data.columns[0]: 'datetime'}, inplace=True)\n",
        "    data['datetime'] = pd.to_datetime(data['datetime'])\n",
        "    return data\n",
        "\n",
        "# Download CAMS.NS data\n",
        "stock_symbol = 'CAMS.NS'\n",
        "data = download_flat_yf(stock_symbol, start='2024-01-01', end='2025-05-04', interval='1d')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Heiken Ashi Transformation (for Supertrend)\n",
        "def heiken_ashi(df):\n",
        "    ha_df = df.copy()\n",
        "    ha_df['ha_close'] = (df['open'] + df['high'] + df['low'] + df['close']) / 4\n",
        "\n",
        "    ha_open = [(df['open'][0] + df['close'][0]) / 2]\n",
        "    for i in range(1, len(df)):\n",
        "        ha_open.append((ha_open[i - 1] + ha_df['ha_close'][i - 1]) / 2)\n",
        "    ha_df['ha_open'] = ha_open\n",
        "\n",
        "    ha_df['ha_high'] = ha_df[['ha_open', 'ha_close', 'high']].max(axis=1)\n",
        "    ha_df['ha_low'] = ha_df[['ha_open', 'ha_close', 'low']].min(axis=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return ha_df\n",
        "\n",
        "data_ha = heiken_ashi(data)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Adding Supertrend Indicator (using Heiken Ashi)\n",
        "\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "def calculate_supertrend(df, period=10, multiplier=3):\n",
        "    atr = df['high'].rolling(window=period).max() - df['low'].rolling(window=period).min()\n",
        "    atr = atr.rolling(window=period).mean()\n",
        "\n",
        "    hl2 = (df['ha_high'] + df['ha_low']) / 2\n",
        "    upperband = hl2 + multiplier * atr\n",
        "    lowerband = hl2 - multiplier * atr\n",
        "\n",
        "    supertrend = [True]\n",
        "    for i in range(1, len(df)):\n",
        "        if df['close'][i] > upperband[i - 1]:\n",
        "            supertrend.append(True)\n",
        "        elif df['close'][i] < lowerband[i - 1]:\n",
        "            supertrend.append(False)\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            supertrend.append(supertrend[i - 1])\n",
        "\n",
        "    df['supertrend'] = supertrend\n",
        "    df['supertrend_direction'] = ['green' if x else 'red' for x in supertrend]\n",
        "    return df\n",
        "\n",
        "data_ha = calculate_supertrend(data_ha)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Adding Money Flow Index (MFI)\n",
        "def calculate_mfi(df, period=14):\n",
        "    typical_price = (df['high'] + df['low'] + df['close']) / 3\n",
        "    money_flow = typical_price * df['volume']\n",
        "\n",
        "    positive_flow = []\n",
        "    negative_flow = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i in range(1, len(typical_price)):\n",
        "        if typical_price[i] > typical_price[i - 1]:\n",
        "            positive_flow.append(money_flow[i])\n",
        "            negative_flow.append(0)\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            negative_flow.append(money_flow[i])\n",
        "            positive_flow.append(0)\n",
        "\n",
        "    mfi = 100 * (pd.Series(positive_flow).rolling(window=period).sum() /\n",
        "                 (pd.Series(positive_flow).rolling(window=period).sum() +\n",
        "                  pd.Series(negative_flow).rolling(window=period).sum()))\n",
        "\n",
        "    mfi = mfi.reindex(df.index, method='bfill')\n",
        "    df['mfi'] = mfi\n",
        "    return df\n",
        "\n",
        "data_ha = calculate_mfi(data_ha)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generating Trading Signals\n",
        "def generate_signals(df):\n",
        "    df['long_entry'] = (\n",
        "        (df['supertrend_direction'] == 'green') &\n",
        "        (df['mfi'] > 50)\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    df['long_exit'] = (\n",
        "        (df['supertrend_direction'] == 'red') |\n",
        "        (df['mfi'] < 50)\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    df['position'] = 0\n",
        "    position = 0\n",
        "    for i in range(len(df)):\n",
        "        if df['long_entry'][i]:\n",
        "            position = 1\n",
        "        elif df['long_exit'][i]:\n",
        "            position = 0\n",
        "        df.at[i, 'position'] = position\n",
        "\n",
        "    return df\n",
        "\n",
        "data_ha = generate_signals(data_ha)\n",
        "\n",
        "# backtest strategy\n",
        "def backtest_strategy(df):\n",
        "    df['returns'] = df['close'].pct_change()\n",
        "    df['strategy_returns'] = df['position'].shift(1) * df['returns']\n",
        "    cumulative_returns = (1 + df[['returns', 'strategy_returns']]).cumprod()\n",
        "    return cumulative_returns\n",
        "\n",
        "cumulative_returns = backtest_strategy(data_ha)\n",
        "# visualize\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(14, 6))\n",
        "plt.plot(cumulative_returns['returns'], label='Buy & Hold', linestyle='--')\n",
        "plt.plot(cumulative_returns['strategy_returns'], label='Strategy X', linewidth=2)\n",
        "plt.title('Backtest of Strategy X on CAMS.NS')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Date')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Cumulative Returns')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.grid(True)\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ],

        "3.4\n",
        "\n",
        "Strategy Y – Incorporating a Complementary Indicator (ATR)\n",
        "Why Add ATR?\n",
        "While Strategy X effectively uses trend (Supertrend) and volume (MFI), it can trigger false signals in low-volatility or sideways markets. To refine the system, Average True Range (ATR) is introduced as a volatility filter:\n",
        "\n",
        "ATR measures market volatility.\n",
        "\n",
        "We use the condition ATR > ATR’s Moving Average (SMA) to ensure we're only trading during expanding volatility.\n",
        "\n",
        "This filters out noise, allowing entries only when strong moves are more likely.\n",
        "\n",
        "Indicator Recap: ATR\n",
        "ATR: Shows the average range (high-low) of price movement over a period (e.g., 14).\n",
        "\n",
        "ATR SMA: A simple moving average of ATR over a longer window (e.g., 20).\n",
        "\n",
        "When ATR > ATR SMA, volatility is rising, signaling a momentum-backed move.\n",
        "\n",
        "Strategy Y – Entry and Exit Rules\n",
        "Entry Conditions (Long Entry Only):\n",
        "Supertrend is green (uptrend).\n",
        "\n",
        "MFI is above 50 (buying pressure).\n",
        "\n",
        "ATR is greater than its SMA (expanding volatility).\n",
        "\n",
        "Timing: Enter at next candle close after all 3 conditions are met.\n",
        "\n",
        "Exit Conditions (for Long Positions):\n",
        "Exit when any one of the following is true:\n",
        "\n",
        "Supertrend turns red (trend reversal), OR\n",
        "\n",
        "MFI drops below 50, OR\n",
        "\n",
        "ATR falls below its SMA (volatility fading)."
      ],

        "#Code implement strategy\n",
        "\n",
        "def calculate_atr(df, period=14):\n",
        "    high_low = df['high'] - df['low']\n",
        "    high_close = np.abs(df['high'] - df['close'].shift())\n",
        "    low_close = np.abs(df['low'] - df['close'].shift())\n",
        "\n",
        "    tr = pd.concat([high_low, high_close, low_close], axis=1).max(axis=1)\n",
        "    atr = tr.rolling(window=period).mean()\n",
        "\n",
        "    df['atr'] = atr\n",
        "    df['atr_sma'] = atr.rolling(window=period).mean()\n",
        "    return df\n",
        "#modifying singal generation with ATR filter\n",
        "data_ha = calculate_atr(data_ha)\n",
        "def generate_strategy_y_signals(df):\n",
        "    df['long_entry_y'] = (\n",
        "        (df['supertrend_direction'] == 'green') &\n",
        "        (df['mfi'] > 50) &\n",
        "        (df['atr'] > df['atr_sma'])\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    df['long_exit_y'] = (\n",
        "        (df['supertrend_direction'] == 'red') |\n",
        "        (df['mfi'] < 50) |\n",
        "        (df['atr'] < df['atr_sma'])\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    df['position_y'] = 0\n",
        "    position = 0\n",
        "    for i in range(len(df)):\n",
        "        if df['long_entry_y'][i]:\n",
        "            position = 1\n",
        "        elif df['long_exit_y'][i]:\n",
        "            position = 0\n",
        "        df.at[i, 'position_y'] = position\n",
        "\n",
        "    return df\n",
        "#backtest strategy Y\n",
        "data_ha = generate_strategy_y_signals(data_ha)\n",
        "def backtest_strategy_y(df):\n",
        "    df['strategy_y_returns'] = df['position_y'].shift(1) * df['returns']\n",
        "    cumulative_returns_y = (1 + df[['returns', 'strategy_returns', 'strategy_y_returns']]).cumprod()\n",
        "    return cumulative_returns_y\n",
        "\n",
        "#visualization of Strategy Y vs X vs Buy & Hold\n",
        "cumulative_returns_y = backtest_strategy_y(data_ha)\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(14, 6))\n",
        "plt.plot(cumulative_returns_y['returns'], label='Buy & Hold', linestyle='--')\n",
        "plt.plot(cumulative_returns_y['strategy_returns'], label='Strategy X')\n",
        "plt.plot(cumulative_returns_y['strategy_y_returns'], label='Strategy Y', linewidth=2)\n",
        "plt.title('Backtest Comparison: Strategy X vs Y vs Buy & Hold')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Date')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Cumulative Returns')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.grid(True)\n",
        "plt.show()\n"

        "3.5\n",
        "\n",
        "Strategy Enhancements\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "Identifying Challenging Market Regimes\n",
        "Despite combining Supertrend, MFI, and ATR, Strategy X and Y can struggle in certain environments:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Sideways/Choppy Markets\n",
        "Supertrend flips frequently → generates whipsaw signals.\n",
        "\n",
        "MFI hovers around 50 → unclear demand/supply dynamics.\n",
        "\n",
        "ATR remains low → lack of meaningful price movement.\n",
        "\n",
        "Effect: False entries and premature exits.\n",
        "\n",
        "2. Low-Volume Phases\n",
        "MFI becomes unreliable (since it uses volume).\n",
        "\n",
        "Supertrend may lag.\n",
        "\n",
        "ATR is suppressed → strategy skips trades, missing possible breakouts.\n",
        "\n",
        "3. News-Driven Gaps\n",
        "Sudden price gaps skip strategy trigger levels.\n",
        "\n",
        "Entries may occur after the move, at suboptimal prices.\n",
        "\n",
        "Effect: Late entries, poor risk-reward.\n",
        "\n",
        "Enhancement Proposals\n",
        "1. Multi-Timeframe Confirmation\n",
        "Check Supertrend on both 1D and 4H charts.\n",
        "\n",
        "Only enter trades if both timeframes agree on direction.\n",
        "\n",
        "Filters noise and avoids countertrend trades.\n",
        "\n",
        "2. ATR Breakout Filter (On top of ATR > ATR SMA)\n",
        "Add a momentum threshold:\n",
        "\n",
        "ATR > 20-day ATR max\n",
        "→ Indicates a breakout or strong momentum phase.\n",
        "\n",
        "3. Volume Surge Filter\n",
        "Add condition:\n",
        "\n",
        "Current volume > 1.5 × 20-day average volume\n",
        "\n",
        "Confirms institutional interest or strong participation.\n",
        "\n",
        "4. Moving Average Trend Confirmation\n",
        "Only take long trades if:\n",
        "\n",
        "Price > 50-period EMA\n",
        "\n",
        "For short trades (if added later):\n",
        "\n",
        "Price < 50 EMA\n",
        "\n",
        "Aligns trades with dominant trend direction.\n",
